*   **Strategic Pivot**: Shift focus to **"Dynamic Factor-Covariance Recovery under GARCH-induced Heteroskedasticity."** Instead of assuming known loadings, implement a rolling-window PCA to extract factors and compare the *tracking error* of the covariance matrix against a GARCH-adjusted shrinkage estimator. This addresses the dataset's actual constraints (latent factors + time-varying volatility) rather than relying on non-existent ground truth parameters.
\end{CRITIC}


